# type(scope): summary (50 chars or less)
# 
# Description of the change (detailed explanation of what and why).
# 
# --- Approved Types ---
# feat:     New feature or standard update.
# fix:      Bug fix or policy correction.
# docs:     Documentation-only changes.
# refactor: Code restructuring (no logic change).
# chore:    Maintenance, dependencies, or boilerplate.
# test:     Adding or updating tests.
# perf:     Performance improvements.
# 
# --- Guidelines ---
# 1. Use the imperative, present tense ("change", not "changed").
# 2. Limit the subject line to 50 characters.
# 3. Capitalize the subject line.
# 4. Do not end the subject line with a period.
# 5. Provide context for the "Why" in the body.
